# Microk8s local setup

## About

This is my Minikube setup for my Mac Silicon

What it does:

5. Asks for a Dynatrace token
6. Containerizes a small Ruby app
7. Pushes the app
8. Pushes the Dynatrace Otel Collector
9. Sends OTel data to Dynatrace

## Install

Install multipass

```
brew install multipass
```

Create a VM

```
multipass launch --name microk8s-vm --mem 4G --disk 40G
```

Shell into it
```
multipass shell microk8s-vm
```

Grab this script and run it

```
git clone https://github.com/mreider/k8s.git
cd k8s
./setup.sh

```

Enter your Dynatrace API endpoint
Enter your Dynatrace Token:

That's it!


